    "# Foundry IQ Demo — Multi-Agent Knowledge Retrieval\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates the **Microsoft Agent Framework** with `AzureAISearchContextProvider`\n",
    "connecting to **two Foundry IQ Knowledge Bases** on the same search service.\n",
    "\n",
    "| Agent | Knowledge Base | Use Case |\n",
    "|-------|---------------|----------|\n",
    "| MVP Summit Concierge | `mvp-summit-knowledge-base` | Session schedule & campus logistics |\n",
    "| Contoso Policy Assistant | `contoso-policy-knowledge-base` | Insurance claims & returns policy |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Prerequisites**: `pip install -r requirements.txt` and fill in `code/.env`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Setup & Configuration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "✓ Connected to Foundry project\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",\n     "from dotenv import load_dotenv\n",\n     "load_dotenv(os.path.join(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(\"__file__\")), \".env\"))\n",\n     "\n",
    "from azure.identity import DefaultAzureCredential, get_bearer_token_provider\n",
    "from azure.ai.projects import AIProjectClient\n",
    "from openai import AzureOpenAI\n",
    "\n",
    "# Configuration\n",
    "PROJECT_ENDPOINT = os.environ[\"AZURE_AI_PROJECT_ENDPOINT\"]\n",
    "SEARCH_ENDPOINT = os.environ[\"AZURE_AI_SEARCH_ENDPOINT\"]\n",
    "OPENAI_ENDPOINT = os.environ[\"AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT\"]\n",
    "MODEL = os.getenv(\"MODEL_DEPLOYMENT\", \"gpt-4.1\")\n",
    "\n",
    "credential = DefaultAzureCredential()\n",
    "project_client = AIProjectClient(endpoint=PROJECT_ENDPOINT, credential=credential)\n",
    "openai_client = project_client.get_openai_client()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✓ Connected to Foundry project\")"
   ]
  },
